,"meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Wolfgang.","German (also <b>Rühle</b>): variant of   Ruhl   or, in some cases, a habitational name from Rühle in Lower Saxony. Compare   Ruehle  .","German: habitational name from Ruhla in Thuringia."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Rule was born about 1535, in Boxted, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She married William Syckerling about 1552, in Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons and 3 daughters. She was buried in Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1535–16 Sep 1576":"umbes 1535–16. september 1576","1533–1599":"1533–1599","1560–1620":"1560–1620","1566–1607":"1566–1607","1569–Female":"1569–Surnud","1572–Male":"1572–Surnud","–1612":"–1612","–1613":"–1613","–Male":"Surnud","1535–1576":"1535–1576","16 Sep 1576":"16. september 1576","1572":"1572","1560":"1560","12 April 1569":"12. aprill 1569","24 April 1566":"24. aprill 1566","1613":"1613","1569":"1569","1535":"1535","1612":"1612","1566":"1566","1599":"1599","1533":"1533","1576":"1576","1620":"1620","about 1535":"umbes 1535","2 January 1560":"2. jaanuar 1560","about 1552":"umbes 1552","1607":"1607","Boxted, Suffolk, England":"Boxted, Suffolk, England","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Boxted, Essex, England":"Boxted, Essex, England"},"fi":{"about 1535–16 Sep 1576":"noin 1535–1